The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | At a glance
                                                                                                                                                                                                     At a glance
                      
	The following is a glance at the mens singles finalists at the French Open:         
	Roger Federer (1, Switzerland)         
	Residence: Oberwil, Switzerland         
	Date of birth: August 8, 1981         
	Place of birth: Basel         
	Height: 6ft 1in         
	Weight: 85kg         
	Turned pro: 1998         
	Plays: Right-handed, one-handed backhand         
	Career prize money: $39,962,037         
	 Playing the French Open for the 10th time. Its the only Grand Slam title he hasnt won.               
	 Will be playing in his third consecutive final at Roland Garros. Lost to Nadal in the 2005 semi-finals, and the 2006 and 2007 finals, making him 0-3 against the Spaniard and 23-0 against everyone else at the French Open the past four years. Is 6-10 overall against Nadal, 1-8 on clay.               
	 Has dropped three sets and 78 games at Roland Garros this year.               
	 Ranked No. 1 since Feb. 2, 2004, a record 227 consecutive weeks. Will be playing in his 15th major final, tied for the fifth-most in tennis history.               
	 Has won 12 Grand Slam titles, five at Wimbledon, four at the US Open, three at the Australian Open. Pete Sampras holds the record with 14.               
	 Has 54 career titles, one this year. Is 32-7 in 2008.               
	 Began working recently with Jose Higueras, who coached Michael Chang and Jim Courier to French Open titles.               
	ROAD TO FINAL           First Round: bt Sam Querrey (US) 6-4, 6-4, 6-3  Second Round: bt Albert Montanes (Esp) 6-7 (5), 6-1, 6-0, 6-4  Third Round: bt Mario Ancic (Cro) 6-3, 6-4, 6-2  Fourth Round: bt Julien Benneteau (Fra) 6-4, 7-5, 7-5  Quarter finals: bt Fernando Gonzalez (24, Chi) 2-6, 6-2, 6-3, 6-4  Semi-finals: bt Gael Monfils (Fra) 6-2, 5-7, 6-3, 7-5    
	Rafael Nadal (2, Spain)         
	Residence: Manacor, Mallorca         
	Date of birth: June 3, 1986         
	Place of birth: Manacor         
	Height: 6ft 1in         
	Weight: 85kg         
	Turned pro: 2001         
	Plays: Left-handed, two-handed backhand         
	Career prize money: $16,276,415               
	 Playing the French Open for the fourth time. Is 27-0 at Roland Garros, winning the last three titles.               
	 Is aiming to become the first player since Bjorn Borg in 1978-1981 to win four consecutive French Open championships. Is first man since Ivan Lendl in 1984-87 to reach four French Open finals in a row.               
	 Since the tournament went international in 1925, only Borg (six total titles) and Henri Cochet (four from 1926 to 1932) have won it four times.               
	 Is 114-2 on clay since 2005. Is 40-0 in best-of-five-set matches on the surface for his career. Has never been pushed to five sets at Roland Garros.               
	 Lost to Federer in 2006 and 2007 Wimbledon finals. Has dropped zero sets and 37 games at Roland Garros this year.               
	 Ranked No. 2 since July 25, 2005  150 consecutive weeks. Has won 26 career titles, including three this year. Is 43-7 this year.               
	 Coached by his uncle, Toni Nadal.               
	ROAD TO FINAL           First Round: bt Thomaz Bellucci (Bra) 7-5, 6-3, 6-1  Second Round: bt Nicolas Devilder (Fra) 6-4, 6-0, 6-1  Third Round: Jarkko Nieminen (26, Fin) 6-1, 6-3, 6-1  Fourth Round: bt Fernando Verdasco (22, Esp) 6-1, 6-0, 6-2  Quarter finals: bt Nicolas Almagro (19, Esp) 6-1, 6-1, 6-1  Semi-finals: bt Novak Djokovic (3, Srb) 6-4, 6-2, 7-6 (3)                                                                                                                           
